# Release workflow (MasterFabric Mac CLI)

When a feature or fix is **done and ready to ship**, do not leave it only as local commits. Finish the release loop before starting unrelated new work.

## Required sequence

1. **Commit** all related changes with a clear message (English).
2. **Bump version** in root `VERSION` (semver patch/minor as appropriate), then `make version-sync` (keeps `AppVersion.current` aligned). Update `Formula/masterfabric.rb` tag URL if present.
3. **Push `main`** to GitHub.
4. **Tag + release** with `gh`:
   - `git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "MasterFabric Mac CLI vX.Y.Z"`
   - `git push origin vX.Y.Z`
   - `gh release create vX.Y.Z --title "vX.Y.Z" --notes "…"`
5. **Only then** start the next feature/fix branch of work.

## Commands (reference)

```bash
echo 'X.Y.Z' > VERSION && make version-sync
git add -A && git commit -m "…" && git push origin main
git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "MasterFabric Mac CLI vX.Y.Z" && git push origin vX.Y.Z
gh release create vX.Y.Z --title "vX.Y.Z" --notes "## …"
```

## Do not

- Ship code to `main` without a matching GitHub release when the change is user-facing.
- Bump `VERSION` without tagging/releasing (or vice versa).
- Commit secrets, real tokens, or personal `chat_id` values.
- Skip `make version-sync` after editing `VERSION`.

## After release

Optionally verify on the machine: `mf update` / `make install`, then `mf version --check --json`.
